Objective

After a long and wonderful career in Acccounting and Real Estate, I made a decision to branch out and find a career I can truly be passionate about. After speaking with a graduate from NSS, I found my drive and passion. I was looking for a career that would not only challenge me, but also be able to impact people in their every day lives. I CAN do something more. After six long and hard working months, I will be graduating the end of March from Nashville Software School. With my new developed skills I hope to bring to a positive vibe to my new work place and learn as much as I can on a day to day basis. I find the tech community in Nashville to be very nurturing and positive and can not wait to see what the future will hold. I am looking for a collaborative agile work environment.

What I Do ?

Nashville Software School aka NSS is a full time, hands on, intensive training program on software development. The first 3 months of the course curriculum covered GitHub, HTML, CSS, Javacript, Jquery, Handlebars, Angular, Phaser. The focus of the front end was group projects with a focus of working together to create a web application. The last three months covered back end development with a focue on Node JS, Express, Ionic, Cordova, Sqlite, web scrapping, MEAN Stack (Mongo, Express, Angular, Node) and test driven development using Mocha and Chai.
